text:
Hey, guys.
I'm on vacation right now
in Wyoming with my family,

and I am about to play
a little game
called First Things First
with me, Olivia Sanabia.

All right, let's get started.
First question.
First celebrity crush you had?

Was Zac Efron
from "High School Musical."

For sure.
First time I met Ruby?

We first met when
we were doing a mix and match

and we were reading
for the parts together.

First app you check when you
wake up in the morning?

Oh, definitely Instagram,
for sure. 100%.
First celebrity you ever met?

The first celeb that I ever met
was Jennifer Garner

when I played her daughter
in my first job ever,
which was a print job.

First thing you watched
in Disney Now?

The first thing
I saw in Disney Now

was old reruns
of "Hannah Montana,"
'cause it's my jam.

First time you saw yourself
on Disney Channel?

Well, my wand ID-- you know,
the thing where you go,

"Hey, I'm Olivia and you're
watching Disney Channel"?

It was playing right before
"High School Musical,"

and that was such
an awesome moment for me.

First time
you went to Disney World?

I went to Disney World
when I was ten years old,
and it was the trip of my life.

I had the best time ever,
and I literally counted down
the days for three months.
First DCOM you ever saw?

Of course,
"High School Musical."
Love it.

First time doing something
that scared you?

I remember when I did
my first production in theater,

and I was so scared
and I was six years old.

But I remember instantly
falling in love with it

the second I got on stage,
and then the nerves went away.
First time on a plane?

Well, I think the first time
I was on a plane

was when I was two years old
and I was going to Hawaii.

And I've heard stories
that I wasn't very good
on the plane for my parents.
So, sorry, Mom and Dad.
I think that's it.
